== French ==
=== Etymology ===
Past participle of 'rouer', ''to break upon a wheel'' or ''to beat harshly'', from the belief that such individuals deserve such a punishment.  'Rouer' derives from the Latin 'rota', ''wheel'', from the Proto-Indo-European 'ret-', ''to run'' or ''to roll''.

=== Noun ===
''masculine form'': '''roué''' (''feminine form'': '''rouée'''; masculine and feminine ''plural'': '''roués''')

#A [[roué]], an individual who sees others only as sex objects